South Africaâ€™s gross domestic product (GDP) contracted by 3.2% in the first quarter, Statistics South Africa (Stats SA) revealed at a press briefing, in Pretoria, on Tuesday. The manufacturing and the mining and quarrying industries were the biggest negative contributors to GDP. The manufacturing industry decreased by 8.8% and contributed -1.1 percentage points to GDP growth. The mining and quarrying industry contracted by 10.8% and contributed -0.8 of a percentage point to GDP growth. Meanwhile, expenditure on real GDP fell by 3.4% in the period, Stats SA reported.